<subSubSection pageId="32" pageNumber="33" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="32.[151,1436,1153,1502]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,319,1369,1394]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Species of average size, contrasted coloration, face yellow with 3 dark spots, dorsal disk of pronotum pale yellow anteriorly; very similar in coloration and external morphology to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Otte" authorityYear="2007" box="[1141,1220,1406,1429]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Cardiodactylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="riga">
<emphasis box="[1141,1220,1406,1429]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">C. riga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, to which it differs by yellow Sc vein (brown in 
<taxonomicName authority="Otte, 2007 a" authorityName="Otte" authorityYear="2007" box="[476,694,1441,1466]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Cardiodactylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="riga">
<emphasis box="[476,555,1442,1465]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">C. riga</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Otte, D." box="[562,694,1441,1466]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" pagination="341 - 400" refId="ref50945" refString="Otte, D. (2007 a) New species of Cardiodactylus from the western Pacific region (Gryllidae: Eneopterinae). Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia, 156, 341 - 400. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1635 / 0097 - 3157 (2007) 156 [341: nsocft] 2.0. co; 2" type="journal article" year="2007">Otte, 2007a</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
) and male genitalia with only one level laterally.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
